Job Description:
CLEARANCE: TS/SCI w/CI Polygraph

WORK SITE: JBAB Bolling AFB

TRAVEL:None

JOB DESCRIPTION:

The Software Engineer shall engineer, design, develop, integrate, test, and deploy solutions to enhance and modernize existing systems and applications and facilitate their migration to an enterprise AWS cloud environment [using both Windows & Linux cloud & server technologies]. The same shall be done for select new applications. Job duties shall also include:
Lead by example, demonstrating a professional, can-do attitude within an integrated project team dependent upon cross-functional teamwork;
Work with developers and engineers to define customer and system requirements and develop solutions and system designs that will scale to meet projected future enterprise requirements;
Analyze the AS-IS code state and the TO-BE end state and recommend modernization/enhancements to improve systems/applications performance and reliability in the AWS environment;
Perform trend analysis to evaluate the overall systems utilization and growth-capability health, performance, and capacity management;
Improve [code] application performance and reliability;
Design and develop software code to add new features to existing web-based applications and create new web-based applications using Java, Python, .xml, and JSON;
Develop solutions to integrate COTS products within the enterprise Data Governance space using Mulesoft Enterprise Service Bus (ESB) and AnyPoint, to exchange and share data[regardless of the technology used, such as:JMS, Web Services, JDBC, HTTP, etc;
Securely integrate APIs and transform and load data between endpoints;
Ensure connectivity with APIs, applications, cloud technology, and data sources;
Recommend and/or engineer and apply programs designed to identify, validate and resolve complex engineering-related problems;
Regularly test applications, apply patches and version updates to maintain strong functionality and optimization, and validate the applications adherence to design specifications and requirements;
Update application design specifications to capture any changes to standards, settings, configuration parameters, etc;
Perform root cause analysis and provide mitigation strategies;
Troubleshoot reported code defects and deficiencies and recommend resolutions;
Debug and resolve application issues and defects;
Configure, administer, and support virtualized AWS server environment;
Deploy, configure, secure, and monitor common services;
Design and update software databases.
EXPERIENCE & QUALIFICATIONS:

EXPERIENCE:
Must have experience leading software engineering and development activities and leading, directing, and managing teams/team members to carry out software development coding, testing, integration, and systems testing;
Solid understanding of and multiple years of experience:
Developing in Python, Java, .xml, and HTML;
Designing, developing, and modifying databases, and experience with various data formats and structures, such as JSON, Neo4J, Postgres SQL, and MongoDB;
Experience supporting each phase of the software development lifecycle; which includes: system planning and research, engineering and design, development and testing, integration and systems testing, deployment, as well as creating and updating a variety of documents;
Experience providing systems/software engineering and development for the DoD, preferable the Intelligence Community within the DoD;
Experience with a wide variety of tools and techniques within a cloud AWS environment, including:
Activiti, Jenkins, Git, REST APIs; and
MuleSoft's Anypoint Platform, especially the Expose Application Functionality (ESB) within an AWS environment.
Experience designing, developing, leading, conducting, and facilitating unit testing, integration testing, systems testing, security testing, functional testing, and user-acceptance testing.
QUALIFICATIONS:
Meet IAM Level II certification requirements (Security+);
Minimum of 2-years' experience in systems engineering;
Minimum of 5 years experience in software/code development.
EDUCATION:
Bachelors in a computer design/development/systems/engineering field;
Education Waiver:
14+ years w/ High School Diploma;
10+ years w/ Bachelors Degree;
7+ years w/ Masters Degree.
